College Bound - TRIO Can Help
Is your child planning to attend college one day? We’re pros, let TRIO help! Your child may be eligible to join a free college prep program at school! We offer college tours, college application assistance, financial aid application assistance, mentoring, workshops for students and families, academic assistance, and career exploration. If you would like to know more about eligibility requirements contact Rose Maes at 970-903-0180, or complete an application online at https://www.fortlewis.edu/about-flc/initiatives/trio-talent-search/apply-for-trio-talent-search.

SENIORS & PARENTS - Do you have questions on the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) and other financial aid available for students?

MHS will host the first-ever Drive-In Financial Aid Information Night on Thursday, October 1, at 6:00PM in the West parking lot in front of the PC. Tiffany and Rose Maes, with TRIO, will be available to help you answer questions while you apply to FAFSA. We will be sending an informational video out in a couple of weeks regarding what FAFSA is, how to create an FSA ID, and what documents are needed to apply. Stay tuned!

Students! What a neat way to explore career options.

Visit Virtual Job Shadow Today!

Access Virtual Job Shadow FOR FREE: VirtualJobShadow.com is a free, comprehensive, multimedia career exploration and planning resource, with topics that include job shadowing and advice videos, job and college search tools, career and interest assessments, and a digital portfolio. Educators and students can create an account at https://www.virtualjobshadow.com/vs3/portals/license/login/46B55CE4-7C48-4789-9D24-4E2B9D0355A8/

ABOUT VIRTUALJOBSHADOW.COM

VirtualJobShadow.com is a highly engaging, fully digital career exploration and workforce development resource for secondary and post-secondary students, opportunity youth, and jobseekers. We bring job shadowing directly to the account-holder, eliminating many of the costs and challenges frequently associated with traditional job shadowing.

Login to your account today to access hundreds of career profiles and videos, along with education and job-search tools, and more.

📌Pre K-12 SUBSTITUTE TEACHERS NEEDED📌

A teacher's license or a substitute certification from the Colorado Department of Education is required. A degree is not required for a one-year CDE Substitute Authorization. Please stop by the District Office for a Substitute Teacher Application Packet.

For information on how to attain a CO Substitute Authorization go to:
http://www.cde.state.co.us/cdeprof/Licensure_SubApp.asp

SUBSTITUTE BUS DRIVERS
Must be available and reliable on short notice and enjoy working with children of all ages. Class B CDL required. We will train and take care of testing necessary to be licensed. Please complete a Bus Driver Application and drop it at the District Office or the Bus Garage.

OTHER SUBSTITUTE POSITIONS
(CUSTODIAL, FOOD SERVICES, PARAPROFESSIONALS, ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANTS)
The district is seeking qualified candidates to fill in occasionally for support positions such as food services, paraprofessionals, administrative assistants and custodial staff. No certification is required.

post_text:
SENIORS:

Colorado Free Application Day is Tuesday, October 13, 2020.

What is Colorado Free Application Day?
For the third year in a row, the Colorado Department of Higher Education is teaming up with colleges and universities across Colorado to waive college application fees for all Colorado students on Tuesday, October 13, 2020. That means if you submit your application between 12:01 a.m. and 11:59 p.m. that day, you can apply for free to any public institution in Colorado and many private institutions as well.

How do I know if I qualify?
All Colorado residents — freshmen, transfers and second bachelor’s candidates — qualify for Colorado Free Application Day. (We’re including Colorado undocumented students as well.)

The free application is available October 13, 2020, only. You must submit your online application that day to receive the waiver.

post_text:
Hopefully the meal service is working for most of you. If you are finding it difficult to get to your designated spot on each Monday, please let us know so we can make other arrangements for you, otherwise, if you have ordered meals for the week, please be sure and pick them up. In town meal pick up is every Monday from 10am to 11am. If you are unsure of your pick up time, if you no longer would like to receive meals, or would like to be added to the list please email mealcount@mancosre6.edu

As we move further into this pandemic we are finding it more and more difficult to get certain items. Please be patient with us as we work through this with our distributors. This may mean we need to get "creative" with what is going home in the lunches. We are trying to make sure that meals that go home are well balanced, healthy meals that meet the state requirements. Thank you for your understanding.

MANCOS SCHOOL DISTRICT CHALLENGE

Ok guys and girls. It is time to put those skills to the test! Introducing the Mancos School District Juggling While Walking Challenge!

You have one week to video yourself juggling while walking. Post your videos by Thursday, April 2nd by 4:00PM. Winners will win $10!!

Submit your video to this post on Facebook with your name and grade level. Tag us and use hashtag #mancosschooldistrictchallenge. post_text: Seniors!
shared_text:
Mancos Creative District
April 1 at 3:24 PM ·

Mancos, CO – Create 81328 Scholarship fund has been established for Mancos High School or home school students graduates. Create 81328 scholarship fund; a program of the Mancos Creative District intends to support college bound arts focused students. Applications are due by April 15, 2020
Scholarship founder, Maggie Goodell said,” When our son was a senior in high school and looking to study art in college he didn’t find scholarships for art.” Mancos, Colorado has a strong and vibrant creative community. We are continuing this legacy by providing financial support to college bound students in the 81328 zip code who have a passion for the arts.”
Create 81328 scholarship has been initially funded by anonymous donors and Mancos Valley Chamber of Commerce.
For more information or to apply, please contact Anne Beach, Mancos Creative District, anne@mancoscreativedistrict.com, 970-715-1774

post_text:
Day 2 of Distance Learning

Mrs. Farrar- Our kitchen table work space...the sign reads "Call out 'Farrar!' if you need to meet."

Piper says she likes being more independent and learning at her own pace.

Cash & Clay: When you’re caught up on your work and need a little exercise.

Aysia enjoyed seeing teachers and students in Google Meets yesterday. But she also likes being in her room to do her work.

Ayden enjoys being at home and is enjoying this experience with distance learning. He also said that Hangout Meets is such a good tool.

Logan...not getting distracted by my classmates!

Teagan is enjoying distance learning because she doesn't have to drive 20 minutes into Mancos everyday, and she can cuddle up in her cozy corner to do her work.

Show us how you do Distance Learning, The BlueJay Way!

Reminder: Monday, March 30th, the district will deliver meals at the bus stops. If you live in town, pick up time will be from 10AM-12PM in front of the high school.

If you live in an area serviced by one of our school busses, meals will be delivered via our bus route. The bus routes will start at 10AM and continue to all the stops. Please make sure you or your students are present at the bus stop for delivery. Please do not approach the bus until your family name has been called. Be mindful of social distancing. The Northside of the highway including Moutain View Trailer Park and the Menefee Overlook Apartments will be at the beginning of the bus stops.

If you live in town, South of Highway 160, you will need to continue picking up your meals each Monday in front of the High School. Pick up time will be from 10AM-12PM.

post_text:
⚠️URGENT ANNOUNCEMENT⚠️

Parents/Guardians:

Today at 4:15PM we received word that Governor Polis has issued a Statewide Mandatory Stay-At-Home order. Beginning at 6AM Thursday, March 26th until April 11th.

Given this new information we want to give the following updates as of 5:32PM, March 25th:

1. Food service delivery will happen as scheduled per our previous announcement.
2. The Thursday and Friday PK-5 scheduled event to hand out learning materials and Chromebooks is postponed until further notice.
3. The scheduled middle school Chromebook hand-out for Thursday, March 26th is postponed until further notice.
4. Retrieving Middle and High school materials is on hold until further notice.
As a leadership team, we will be meeting remotely tomorrow at 9AM to discuss our scheduled March 30th roll out of Distance Learning. More details on this will be provided as soon as we determine what is best for our staff and students.

post_text:
Congratulations to the 212 students from Colorado, New Mexico, Utah, and Wyoming who were selected as 2020 Daniels Scholars!

Applying for the Daniels Scholarship Program is a competitive process with many qualified candidates. This year, they received 2,265 applications. Local community and business leaders interviewed 456 finalists and 212 of those were selected as Daniels Scholars. Out of that 212 selected for the Daniels, Mancos High School had two recipients!!

Congratulations to Sage Franks and John Lund!

You can also submit your videos by email to Mrs. Eschallier: leschallier@mancosre6.edu or Mr. Gardner: jgardner@mancosre6.edu. Don’t forget to include your name and grade level. Show us what you got!

Your entry submitted earns you one ticket in a random drawing. One winner will be selected from each grade level.

Rules:
1. Students must be outside!
2. Must have 3 items to juggle that resembles a ball. (Tennis balls, oranges)
3. The video must show the full person juggling while walking.
#mancosschooldistrictchallenge #quarantinechallange #socialdistancechallange
text:
MANCOS SCHOOL DISTRICT CHALLENGE

Ok guys and girls. It is time to put those skills to the test! Introducing the Mancos School District Juggling While Walking Challenge!

You have one week to video yourself juggling while walking. Post your videos by Thursday, April 2nd by 4:00PM. Winners will win $10!!

How to enter:
Submit your video to this post on Facebook with your name and grade level. Tag us and use hashtag #mancosschooldistrictchallenge. You can also submit your videos by email to Mrs. Eschallier: leschallier@mancosre6.edu or Mr. Gardner: jgardner@mancosre6.edu. Don’t forget to include your name and grade level. Show us what you got!

Your entry submitted earns you one ticket in a random drawing. One winner will be selected from each grade level.

Rules:
1. Students must be outside!
2. Must have 3 items to juggle that resembles a ball. (Tennis balls, oranges)
3. The video must show the full person juggling while walking.
#mancosschooldistrictchallenge #quarantinechallange #socialdistancechallange

post_text:
‼IMPORTANT MESSAGE‼

Today, March 18th, Governor Polis signed an executive order closing schools until April 17th. The district's leadership team will meet this Friday to plan our next steps forward on how we will offer ongoing online school and learning opportunities to our students as well as providing meals. This also means that all sports and extracurricular activities (including prom) are postponed until further notice.

Thank you to our parents, students, staff, and community for your flexibility and patience while we continue to ensure the best possible safe and effective learning environment.

Please stay tuned for further details.

Good afternoon!
I have some exciting news!
Great News! Mati McDaniel, aka Matilda514 (on artsonia,) from Mancos School Re6, has been selected as a finalist for this week's "Artist of the Week" award for the 10th-12th age group. The finalist who receives the most online votes between now and Saturday, February 01 will be selected as our "Artist of the Week."

To view the finalists and cast your vote, simply click on the link below. Voting is limited to one vote per computer per day for each age group!

http://www.artsonia.com/aotw/vote/

Please help Mati become the "Artist of the Week," so that she will be featured on the Artsonia homepage and will receive a commemorative plaque from Artsonia. Not to mention the art program will receive a Blick Art Material $100 gift certificate, and Mati wins $50 for her hard work.

Please spread the word! Thank you!

--

Alys Hansen
Art Teacher K-12
Mancos RE6
____________________________
This is dedication. A life lived for art is never a life wasted. ~Macklemore

post_text:
High school juniors are invited to apply for the 2020 American Legion Colorado Boys State Program. At Colorado Boys State these young men will experience real life America while they create and operate their own cities, counties and state governments. In a complete "Hands On" environment the boys will interact with their peers from all across Colorado to share concerns, ideas and come to agreements on what and how to operate their state as they develop and demonstrate their leadership skills.

This fun and educational program is conducted on the campus of University of Colorado Springs (UCCS) from May 30 thru June 4, 2020.

The American Legion Auxiliary Colorado Girls State Program is a unique and exciting government-in-action learning program that encourages high school juniors to become empowered and knowledgeable leaders. For more information:
http://www.alacolorado.com/girls-state.html

December 16, 2019 at 5:52 PM ·

We now have reports of a norovirus-like illness in Montezuma County. This further emphasizes the need for proper cleaning and handwashing. Wash your hands, wash your hands, wash your hands! If you have a gastrointestinal illness with vomiting and diarrhea, stay at home. This may be hard during the holidays, but it also keeps others from contracting the virus. See our previous posts for more information and cleaning suggestions for norovirus.

Mancos Cross Country
October 13, 2019 at 1:39 PM ·

Regionals!

On Thursday, the high school teams will leave at 4:30 pm to travel to Delta for the 2A Region 4 Championship on Friday. We will spend the night in Montrose on Thursday night before making the trip to Delta on Friday morning. We will return Friday after the races.

Event schedule -
2A girls - 2:30
4A girls - 3:10
2A boys - 3:50
4A boys - 4:30

Directions - https://bit.ly/35sbALg - the race is at Confluence Park in Delta

This is the race to see who qualifies for the 2A Colorado Cross Country State Championship in Colorado Springs on Saturday, October 26th. To qualify, we need to be one of the top 5 teams (out of 15) or be in the top 15 individually at the regional race.

We hope to see you there!
